Language name: RESIGARO
Language number: 6838
Alternate names: 
Classification: S. American, Macro-Arawakan
Comments: Resigaro has a two level tone system. Sequences 
of like or unlike vowels may bear differing tones. Only 
/?/ may appear syllable finally. Voiced plosives but not 
not affricates have optional prenasalization "particularly 
in initial position or for emphasis". /w/ and /j/ have 
voiced fricative allophones.

Sources: 

Allin, T.R. 1976. A Grammar of Resigaro. Summer Institute 
of Linguistics, Horsleys Green, High Wycombe, 
Buckinghamshire, England.